    "Problem Formalization": "Solve the 2D Helmholtz equation ∇²u + k²u = f in a staircase-shaped domain Ω with Dirichlet/Robin/impedance boundary data (type unspecified—must be confirmed; workflow assumes known boundary condition g on ∂Ω). The domain spans ~10 wavelengths (L ≈ 10λ, λ = 2π/k). The staircase boundary creates multiple re-entrant corners, each with interior angle α = 3π/2. The wavenumber k is not given explicitly but is implied by the 10-wavelength span; it must be specified to set the point budget. The PDE residual loss is L_r = (1/N_r)Σ|∇²u_θ + k²u_θ − f|², the boundary loss is L_b = (1/N_b)Σ|B[u_θ] − g|², and the total loss is L = w_r·L_r + w_b·L_b with tunable weights.",
    "Physics Constraints": "(i) Re-entrant corner singularity: at each corner with interior angle α = 3π/2, the homogeneous solution has a leading singular mode u_s ∝ r^(π/α)·sin(πθ/α) = r^(2/3)·sin(2θ/3) in local polar coordinates (r,θ) centered on the corner. The gradient ∇u_s ∝ r^(-1/3), which is singular but square-integrable (H^{1+2/3-ε} regularity). Higher singular modes r^(2n/3)·sin(2nθ/3) for n≥2 are smoother. The k² term modifies the singular structure at O(kr) but the r^(2/3) leading behavior persists. (ii) Radiation/decay: if any boundary is open, a radiation condition or PML is needed (not specified—must confirm). (iii) Oscillatory constraint: the solution oscillates with period λ, requiring sufficient collocation density to resolve phase. (iv) Energy balance: |∇u|² and k²|u|² must satisfy Rellich-type identities; violating this signals spectral bias failure.",
    "Model Choice": "A single modified MLP with Fourier feature encoding, using a singularity-subtracted ansatz: u(x) = Σ_i ψ_i(r_i)·r_i^(2/3)·sin(2θ_i/3)·A_i + N_θ(x), where i indexes re-entrant corners, (r_i,θ_i) are local polar coordinates at corner i, ψ_i is a smooth radial cutoff (ψ_i=1 for r_i<0.2λ, ψ_i=0 for r_i>0.5λ), A_i are learnable amplitude parameters, and N_θ is the network representing the smooth remainder. The network uses Fourier feature mapping γ(v)=[cos(Bv),sin(Bv)] with B sampled at frequencies up to ~4k to mitigate spectral bias, followed by a 6-layer MLP of width 256 with tanh activations. This decomposition ensures the network only represents the smooth part v∈H², avoiding approximation of the r^(2/3) singularity. If the number of re-entrant corners exceeds ~20, the cutoff overlap must be checked; corners closer than λ apart require merged cutoff regions.",
    "Training Strategy": "Point budget (40,000 total) split: (a) Bulk interior: 20,000 points uniformly sampled in Ω, yielding ~20,000/(60λ²) ≈ 333 points/λ², i.e., √333 ≈ 18.3 ppw in each direction—sufficient for ~10λ oscillations with PINN oversampling. (b) Corner refinement: 12,000 points concentrated in annular zones 0 < r_i < 0.4λ around each re-entrant corner. Assuming 16 corners, that is 750 points/corner, distributed with density ∝ r^(-1/3) (matching the gradient singularity) via inverse-transform sampling from p(r)∝r^(-1/3) on [0,0.4λ]. (c) Boundary: 8,000 points on ∂Ω, with 4,000 on straight segments (uniform) and 4,000 concentrated near corners (within 0.3λ of each corner along the boundary). Training uses Adam optimizer with learning rate 10⁻³ for 20k steps, then L-BFGS for 10k steps. Loss weights: w_r=1, w_b=100 (boundary accuracy is critical for well-posedness). Residual-based adaptive weighting: after 5k steps, reweight corner-zone residuals by factor 2 if corner L_r > 2×bulk L_r. Learning rate cosine-annealed in the Adam phase. Gradient clipping at norm 1.0 to stabilize training near singular corners.",
    "Validation Failure Risks": "(1) Spectral bias: the network may fail to learn high-frequency oscillations at 10λ scale. Mitigation: monitor the pointwise Helmholtz residual spectrum; if energy at wavenumber k is <50% of DC component after 10k steps, increase Fourier feature bandwidth or switch to a multi-scale Fourier architecture. (2) Corner singularity under-resolution: if the cutoff-subtracted ansatz does not fully capture the singularity (e.g., higher-order modes r^(4/3) matter), the residual near corners will plateau. Mitigation: add a second learnable singular mode r^(4/3)·sin(4θ/3) per corner if corner residual exceeds 5× bulk residual at convergence. (3) Missing boundary condition type: if Robin/impedance conditions are present but treated as Dirichlet, the solution will be wrong everywhere. Must confirm BC type before training. (4) Validation plan—report metrics separately: Corner zones (r_i < 0.3λ): report L² error, H¹ error, and recovered singularity coefficient |A_i − A_i^ref| (if analytical reference exists). Bulk (r_i > 0.5λ for all corners): report relative L² error, relative H¹ error, and phase error max|arg(u)−arg(u_ref)|. Global: report total L² error and the ratio corner_residual/bulk_residual (target <3). If no analytical reference, use cross-validation with a refined FEM solve (h-FEM with p=4 elements and corner mesh grading r^0.4) on the same geometry as ground truth. (5) Generalization: the fixed point budget may be insufficient if the staircase has >20 re-entrant corners or if the wavenumber is higher than assumed; in that case, reduce corner allocation per corner and increase Fourier feature density, accepting higher corner error."
