    "Physics Constraints": "Across each permeability interface Γ_int: (1) h is continuous — this is a physical requirement from pressure equilibrium and must be enforced as a constraint; (2) the normal flux K∂h/∂n is continuous — this is mass conservation across the interface. Since K jumps by a factor of 100 (K₂/K₁ = 100), the normal derivative of h must jump inversely: (∂h/∂n)₂/(∂h/∂n)₁ = K₁/K₂ = 1/100 = 0.01. The factor by which the normal derivative jumps is 0.01. The tangential derivative ∂h/∂t is continuous (since h is continuous and the tangential direction is along the interface). These interface conditions are encoded in the weak form implicitly (flux continuity) and must be enforced explicitly for h continuity. Additional constraints: boundary conditions on ∂Ω, and the PDE residual K_i∇²h = 0 within each subdomain.",
